----------------------------- in this code there are 3 Errors ---------------------------

age = (input("How old are you?")
if age > 18:
print("You can drive at age {age}.")

note :
some error console tells you but some not

--------------------------------- Expected code -------------------------------------------

age = int(input("How old are you?"))
if age > 18:
  print(f"You can drive at age {age}.")
  
  
solve Errors are :
 1. types conversion error str to int.
 2. indentation error.
 3. last invisible error - ["You can drive at age {age}."] to [f"You can drive at age {age}."] msg error.[ age not display ].
